    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-06-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <head>No. 219.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hale</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bassett</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-06-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 26,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 106.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 131, of the 10th
                            instant, relative to the Jastram affair, has been received. The
                            Department congratulates you that <pb facs="0381" n="285" xml:id="pg_285"/> the energy and perseverance with which you have
                            followed up that difficult case has at last been crowned with success,
                            and that it has been adjusted upon a basis compatible with the honor of
                            both Governments.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CHARLES HALE,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting
                                Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
